Solved Practical: Searching Files using File Explorer, Installing Application to computer, Create Shortcut of that application to desktop.

Solution - 
Using File Explorer:
•	Click on the Start menu in the bottom-left corner of your screen.
•	Select File Explorer from the list of options.
•	In the File Explorer window, locate the search box at the top right corner.
•	Type in your search query, such as "report.docx" or keywords related to the file you are looking for.
•	Press Enter to start the search.
File Explorer will display all files and folders that match your search criteria, allowing you to easily locate your desired file.

Application Installation
Downloading and installing an application:
Example: Installing Google Chrome
•	Open your web browser and navigate to the Google Chrome website.
•	Look for the Download Chrome button and click on it.
•	Once the download is complete, locate the downloaded file (usually named something like "ChromeSetup.exe") and double-click to run it.
•	Follow the on-screen instructions in the installation wizard to proceed with the installation.
•	During the installation process, you may be prompted to choose installation options, such as creating a desktop shortcut for Google Chrome

Creating a Shortcut:
Example: Creating a shortcut for Microsoft Word
•	Click on the Start menu in the bottom-left corner of your screen.
•	Find and right-click on Microsoft Word in the list of programs.
•	Select More > Open file location to navigate to where Microsoft Word is installed.
•	Right-click on the Microsoft Word application icon, then choose Send to > Desktop (create shortcut).
•	A shortcut icon for Microsoft Word will appear on your desktop, allowing you to quickly access it whenever needed.
